<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-09T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-09T22:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.248/10–644: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-09T23:00:00-04:00">October 9, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2777. ReLegs 3007, October 6, 11 a.m. from Eddy. For Eddy. Please
                                report nature, extent and dates of British airfield survey at
                                Dhahran referred to in your message from Cairo.</p>
                            <p>Please state also whether at any time King Abdul Aziz suggested that
                                we consult with the British regarding the proposed field at
                                Dhahran.</p>
                            <p>Dhahran’s no. 7, October 4<note n="19" xml:id="d721fn19">Not
                                    printed.</note> not yet received by Department. Sent to Cairo,
                                repeated to Jidda.<note n="20" xml:id="d721fn20">Repeated to Jidda
                                    as telegram 207. In his telegram 302, October 11, 11 a.m., the
                                    Minister in Saudi Arabia reported that the “King at no time
                                    suggested our consultation with British regarding Dhahran
                                    field.” (890F.248/10–1144)</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>